function [ output ] = DVImgCreate( Stream,FileName,NX,NY,NZ,NW,NT,PixSizeX,PixSizeY,PixSizeZ,ImgSequence,PixDataType,ExtHeaderType )

if Stream == 0
    helpdlg('Creates a blank image with the parameters explained below: Stream.  FileName is the full path of the new files location.  Note that if the folder path specified does not exist, MATLAB will not create it and can sometimes crash.  NX is the images X dimension in pixels.  NY is the images Y dimension in pixels.  NZ is the images Z dimension in pixels.  NW is the number of channels (wavelengths) in the image.  NT is the number of time points in the image.  PixSizeX sets the size of each pixel in the X dimension, in microns.  PixSizeY sets the size of each pixel in the Y dimension, in microns.  PixSizeZ sets the size of each pixel in the Z dimension, in microns.  ImgSequence sets the order of the sections within the image. 0=ZTW, 1=WZT and 2=ZWT. 2, ZWT, is the most common.  PixDataType is the data type the pixels of the image should be encoded with (see DVImgGetPixDataType for more information on the possible types).  ExtHeaderType defines whether an extended header will be created within the image.  If it is 0 no extended header will be created, and if it is 1, a standard extended header will be created.  Note that without an extended header functions such as DVImgGetPosX and DVImgSetPhotoSen that require a ZWT position will be unavailable.','int DVImgCreate(int Stream, char FileName,int NX,int NY,int NZ,int NW,int NT,double PixSizeX,double PixSizeY,double PixSizeZ,int ImgSequence,int PixDataType,int ExtHeaderType)');
else
    output = calllib(DVImgLibName,'DVImgCreate',Stream,FileName,NX,NY,NZ,NW,NT,PixSizeX,PixSizeY,PixSizeZ,ImgSequence,PixDataType,ExtHeaderType);
    DVImgPrintErrText(output);
end
